                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2 text-primary">The X-Factor: Automated Reporting</h3>
                    <p class="text-accent mb-4">To take the analysis a step further, the R script was enhanced with an automated reporting feature. The script doesn't just create charts; it analyzes its own findings to generate a dynamic, written summary of key insights, turning code into a communicative tool.</p>
                    <div class="bg-primary text-secondary p-4 rounded-lg shadow-inner h-96 overflow-y-auto">
                        <pre class="text-sm whitespace-pre-wrap">--- Automated Analysis of FTSE 100 ---

A positive long-term trend is suggested, with 10 of 12 months showing a positive median return.

Seasonal Strengths:
- The months with the highest average returns are typically: April, December, November.
- This aligns with the well-documented "Santa Claus Rally" phenomenon in Q4.

Seasonal Weaknesses:
- The months with the lowest average returns are typically: June, September, January.
- This provides strong evidence for the market anomaly known as the "September Effect".

Volatility Insights:
- The most volatile months (largest return range) are: October, September, March.
- The least volatile months (smallest return range) are: August, December, May.

IMPORTANT DISCLAIMER:
This analysis is based on historical data. Past performance is not an indicator of future results. This is not financial advice.
                        </pre>
